                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1002">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.79611 Pangborn-Herndon Flight/143:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shidehara</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Toyko</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-06">October 6,
                            1931</date>?]<lb/>[Received October 6—4:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Now that the ocean between us has been bridged by one continuous flight, accept
                    my warm congratulations on the event and on the intrepidity, skill and patience
                    which have enabled Messrs. Pangborn and Herndon to achieve this memorable result
                    which will always remain a landmark in the history of aviation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kijuro Shidehara</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
